 {"id":"rust_proxy-skx","title":"Implement direct fallback degradation policy","description":"## Implement Direct Fallback Policy

### Overview

Implement the "direct" degradation policy that bypasses the proxy entirely when all proxies are unhealthy, connecting directly to targets.

### Why This Exists

Some use cases prioritize availability over proxy enforcement:
- Development environments where proxy is optional
- Non-sensitive traffic where direct connection is acceptable
- Fallback for proxy infrastructure failures

### Security Considerations

**This policy is dangerous and requires explicit opt-in:**
- Direct connections bypass proxy security controls
- May expose client IP to targets
- May bypass audit logging
- Should NEVER be default

### Implementation

```rust
impl DegradationPolicy {
    async fn handle_direct(&self, target: &str, config: &AppConfig) -> Result<TcpStream> {
        // Verify direct fallback is explicitly enabled
        if !config.settings.allow_direct_fallback {
            anyhow::bail!(
                "Direct fallback requested but allow_direct_fallback is false. \
                 Set allow_direct_fallback = true in config to enable."
            );
        }

        tracing::warn!(
            target = %target,
            "DIRECT CONNECTION: All proxies failed, connecting directly. \
             This bypasses proxy security controls."
        );

        // Connect directly without proxy
        let stream = TcpStream::connect(target).await
            .context("Direct connection failed")?;

        Ok(stream)
    }
}
```

### Configuration

```toml
[settings]
# Required: must be true for direct policy to work
allow_direct_fallback = true

# Set the policy
degradation_policy = "direct"
```

### Logging Requirements

When direct fallback activates, MUST log:
- WARNING level (not info/debug)
- Target being connected to directly
- That proxy controls are being bypassed
- Suggestion to investigate proxy health

### Testing

1. Verify direct works when allow_direct_fallback = true
2. Verify direct FAILS when allow_direct_fallback = false (even if policy is "direct")
3. Verify warning is logged
4. Verify actual direct connection succeeds

### Acceptance Criteria

- [ ] Direct policy connects without proxy
- [ ] Requires allow_direct_fallback = true
- [ ] Logs WARNING when activating
- [ ] Clear error when allow_direct_fallback = false
- [ ] Works with all target types (hostname:port, IP:port)","status":"open","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","assignee":"","owner":"jeff141421@gmail.com","created_at":"2026-01-18T19:56:06.957540111Z","created_by":"Dicklesworthstone","updated_at":"2026-01-18T19:56:06.957540111Z","compaction_level":0}
